obo:ECO_0005589  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_268  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Researchers found an enrichment of Crk-L in mouse adult and developing neuromuscular synapses by performing immunostaining using an antibody against Crk-L. Staining was found in synapses identified using alpha-Bungarotoxin-594 to label AChRs. Imaging was performed using confocal microscopy.\n\n10/4/2017 Pim:\n- \"extrinsic component...\" selected because the paper shows recruitment of Crk-L to the plasma membrane via interaction with another protein.. Experimental description: Experiments were done in mouse myotubes/muscles.\nFrom M&M: \"For protein identification, the digests were analyzed\nby LC/ESI-MS/MS, using a nanoAquity UPLC coupled directly\nto a Q-TOF Premier MS (Waters). The proteins were identified\nusing MASCOT (MatrixScience) to search the NCBInr mouse-\nrat protein sequence database\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0575-6950" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1585-539X" ;
        dc:date           "2017-04-10" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_268" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

